cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on neural architecture search (NAS) for image classification tasks, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of weight sharing, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) tasks, falling under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a Bayesian approach to NAS, which is a common technique in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE).
